         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">British New Guinea. ¶ Granville ¶ Now Port Moresby, PNG. ¶ 16th July 1887 ¶ My dear Baron — ¶  ¶ Mr Cuthbertson has presented to me your letter of recommendation on behalf of the Royal Geographical So...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.07.16b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Douglas</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A36 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; margin-left: 0.493in; text-indent: -0.493in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">British New Guinea.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Granville<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Port Moresby, PNG.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16th July 1887</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Cuthbertson has presented to me your letter of recommendation on behalf of the Royal Geographical Society of Victoria<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You may rely upon my doing every thing I can to assist him in carrying out his explorations, and I believe that I shall be able to give him substantial help<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>On 12 July 1887, Douglas wrote to Cuthbertson: 'Baron von Mueller's letter which you have presented to me will of course insure for you my hearty cooperation in the work entrusted to you by the Royal Geographical Society of Victoria. I shall be happy to place Mr George Hunter's services at your disposal for a time, and this I am sure will be a material assistance to you in dealing with the natives. I need scarcely assure you, I think, that I wish you every success. You have an arduous task before you, and somewhat insufficient means, I fear, for the purpose of accomplishing the great ascent, but if energy and intelligence combined with a fine vigorous constitution wil suffice you ought to succeed'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(A36, Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of NSW, Sydney).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Robert Hunter and Mr Hartman of Toowoomba<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld, where Carl Hartmann had a nursery.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have just come in after a rather successful excursion to the summits of the Range near Mount Obree<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NG. See C. Hartmann to M, August 1887 (in this edition as 87-08-00b). See also W. Lawes to M, 21 September 1887, where Hunter is reported to have gone out again with Cuthbertson.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yrs very faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Douglas</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">K.C.M.G.</p>
         </div>
